<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web">

  <ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="..\LpmSim.Core\LpmSim.Core.csproj" />
    <ProjectReference Include="..\LpmSim.Data\LpmSim.Data.csproj" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="ClosedXML" Version="0.104.2" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.Negotiate" Version="9.0.3" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Identity.Web" Version="4.8.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Identity.Web.UI" Version="4.8.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="MudBlazor" Version="7.15.0" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>net9.0</TargetFramework>
    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
    <UserSecretsId>d895eeb3-6c53-45d7-99d2-1c4f7ead54ee</UserSecretsId>
    <!-- App version surfaced in the sidebar footer. Bump on each release;
         AssemblyInformationalVersion is what Assembly.GetCustomAttribute
         reads at runtime. See CHANGELOG.md at the repo root for the
         per-version release notes. -->
    <Version>1.14.98</Version>
    <AssemblyVersion>1.14.98.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>1.14.98.0</FileVersion>
    <InformationalVersion>1.14.98 (Gap by UPC — persist PalletCategories + LpmMonths on LpmSimBatch so the report replays exactly what the allocator filtered. Migration 059 adds two NULL-able columns to dbo.LPMSIM_Batch: PalletCategories (varchar(500)) and LpmMonths (varchar(200)). GenerateAsync stamps them from req.PalletCategories / req.LpmMonths at Generate time. GetItemAllocationGapAsync reads them and applies the same PalletCategory IN(...) + LPMDt month-range / endExclusive cap the allocator's ReadBoxesAsync uses. Plus the small LPM endExclusive cap fix (was missing, allowed future-dated LPM boxes through). Pre-1.14.98 batches still over-count (NULL filters = no restriction) — flag in CHANGELOG.)</InformationalVersion>
  </PropertyGroup>

</Project>
